  "commentary": "With SPX at 7102.14 sitting just below the max negative gamma strike at 7110, dealers are likely stepping in as buyers here, providing support and dampening downside momentum. The PIN regime with strong positive gamma walls at 7150 and 7200 suggests dealers will aggressively sell any rallies toward those levels, creating a natural ceiling. Key levels to watch are 7110 (current support from dealer buying) and 7150 (first major resistance where dealer selling intensifies).\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7110 support and 7150 resistance with limited breakout potential.",
